(5, 2, NULL, 6, 25, NULL, 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Labrador Retriever', 'labrador-retriever', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(13, 13, 13); font-family: Söhne, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The Labrador Retriever, renowned for its friendly demeanor and unwavering loyalty, stands as one of the most beloved canine companions worldwide. With a sturdy build and an expressive face, Labradors epitomize the quintessential family dog. Their coats come in three classic colors: black, chocolate, and yellow, each adding to their charm. Labradors are known for their intelligence and eagerness to please, making them highly trainable for various tasks, from assistance work to search and rescue missions. Their innate love for water and retrieving instincts harken back to their origins as fishing and hunting aides in Newfoundland, Canada. Despite their playful nature, Labradors possess a gentle disposition, especially around children, making them ideal family pets. Their boundless energy and zest for life ensure they thrive in active households, relishing outdoor adventures and playtime. Labradors excel in forming deep emotional bonds with their human companions, often serving as steadfast emotional support animals. With their infectious enthusiasm and unwavering devotion, Labradors continue to win hearts as cherished members of countless households worldwide.</span><br></p>', '428', NULL, NULL, 300, 1, 'new', 'original', '+447464736755', 0, 'Moffat, United Kingdom', 55.3780510, -3.4359730, 0, 504, 1, 1, '2024-06-11 03:12:03', NULL, '2024-04-27 01:57:28', '2024-11-13 06:06:07'),
